+# Spec: Federation Aggregated Visibility
+
+## Purpose
+
+The federation layer already pushes and stores measurement summaries from every node, and `federation_service.get_aggregated_node_stats` already aggregates them into a fleet-wide view. But the web dashboard shows only node identity (hostname, status, providers list) — provider health, speed, and alerts are invisible. This spec surfaces that data on the `/federation` page so operators and contributors can see, at a glance, whether the network is healthy and which providers need attention.
+
+This is the proof layer: it turns "federation is wired up" into "federation is visibly working."
+
+## Requirements
+
+- [ ] **R1**: `GET /api/federation/nodes/stats` — already exists; verify response shape includes `providers` (dict keyed by slot_id → `{success_rate, avg_duration_s, sample_count, needs_attention, node_count}`), `alerts` (list), `total_measurements`, `window_days`, `nodes` (dict).
+- [ ] **R2**: Add `GET /api/federation/nodes/{node_id}/stats` — returns provider breakdown for a single node. Reuses `get_aggregated_node_stats` filtered by `node_id`, or a new `get_node_provider_stats(node_id)` helper in `federation_service.py`. Returns 404 if the node is not registered.
+- [ ] **R3**: Web `/federation` page adds a `loadNetworkStats()` async function that fetches `/api/federation/nodes/stats` with `cache: 'no-store'`.
+- [ ] **R4**: Web `/federation` page renders a **Network Provider Health** panel (new `NetworkProviderPanel` component inline or in same file) above the node list. Panel shows:
+  - Summary row: `total_measurements` · `window_days`-day window · alert count badge (amber if >0)
+  - One row per provider: name, success rate (color-coded green ≥80% / amber 50–79% / red <50%), avg duration, sample count.
+  - Collapsible alert list when alerts are present.
+- [ ] **R5**: Each node card in the existing node grid adds a mini provider health row — for each provider in `node.providers`, show a colored dot (green/amber/red) based on that provider's `success_rate` from the network stats response. If no stats data is available for a provider, show a grey dot.
+- [ ] **R6**: Add tests in `api/tests/test_flow_federation.py` covering:
+  - `GET /api/federation/nodes/stats` returns 200 with expected keys when no measurements exist.
+  - `GET /api/federation/nodes/{node_id}/stats` returns 404 for unknown node.
+  - `GET /api/federation/nodes/{node_id}/stats` returns 200 with correct provider data after measurements are pushed.
+
