+## Verification Scenarios
+
+### Scenario 1 — Network stats returns correct shape when no measurements exist
+
+```bash
+# Register a node first
+curl -s -X POST http://localhost:8000/api/federation/nodes \
+  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
+  -d '{"node_id":"test-node-1","hostname":"test.local","os_type":"linux","providers":["claude"],"capabilities":{}}'
+
+# Fetch network stats
+curl -s http://localhost:8000/api/federation/nodes/stats | python3 -m json.tool
+```
+
+Expected: HTTP 200; response contains `"providers"`, `"alerts"`, `"total_measurements"`, `"window_days"` keys; `total_measurements` is `0`; `providers` is `{}`.
+
+### Scenario 2 — Per-node stats 404 for unknown node
+
+```bash
+curl -s -o /dev/null -w "%{http_code}" \
+  http://localhost:8000/api/federation/nodes/no-such-node-xyz/stats
+```
+
+Expected output: `404`
+
+### Scenario 3 — Per-node stats 200 after measurements pushed
+
+```bash
+NODE_ID="test-node-1"
+
+# Push measurement summary
+curl -s -X POST http://localhost:8000/api/federation/nodes/${NODE_ID}/measurements \
+  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
+  -d '{
+    "summaries": [{
+      "decision_point": "provider_spec",
+      "slot_id": "claude",
+      "sample_count": 10,
+      "success_count": 9,
+      "failure_count": 1,
+      "avg_duration_s": 38.0,
+      "dedup_key": "test-node-1:provider_spec:claude:2026-04-25"
+    }]
+  }'
+
+# Fetch per-node stats
+curl -s http://localhost:8000/api/federation/nodes/${NODE_ID}/stats | python3 -m json.tool
+```
+
+Expected: HTTP 200; `providers.claude.success_rate` is `0.9`; `total_measurements` is `10`.
+
+### Scenario 4 — Network-wide stats aggregates across two nodes
+
+```bash
+# Register second node and push its measurements
+curl -s -X POST http://localhost:8000/api/federation/nodes \
+  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
+  -d '{"node_id":"test-node-2","hostname":"test2.local","os_type":"darwin","providers":["claude"],"capabilities":{}}'
+
+curl -s -X POST http://localhost:8000/api/federation/nodes/test-node-2/measurements \
+  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
+  -d '{
+    "summaries": [{
+      "decision_point": "provider_spec",
+      "slot_id": "claude",
+      "sample_count": 20,
+      "success_count": 14,
+      "failure_count": 6,
+      "avg_duration_s": 55.0,
+      "dedup_key": "test-node-2:provider_spec:claude:2026-04-25"
+    }]
+  }'
+
+# Check network stats
+curl -s http://localhost:8000/api/federation/nodes/stats | python3 -c "
+import json,sys
+d=json.load(sys.stdin)
+c=d['providers'].get('claude',{})
+print('node_count:', c.get('node_count'))
+print('total_measurements:', d['total_measurements'])
+"
+```
+
+Expected: `node_count: 2`, `total_measurements: 30`
+
+### Scenario 5 — Web page renders without crash when stats returns empty
+
+```bash
+# Build and check Next.js SSR (assumes dev server running)
+curl -s -o /dev/null -w "%{http_code}" http://localhost:3000/federation
+```
+
+Expected: `200` (page renders; no 500 even when no federation data)
+
+## Out of Scope
+
+- Real-time push / WebSocket updates to the dashboard
+- Historical trend charts (time-series graphs over days/weeks)
+- Per-task-type breakdown visible in the web UI (API returns it; web shows provider-level only)
+- Authentication / access control on stats endpoints
+- Local-node `/api/providers/stats` integration into the federation view (different data path)
+
+## Risks and Assumptions
+
+- **Risk**: `get_aggregated_node_stats` in the service is already ~100 lines; the per-node variant should filter it, not fork it. If the service function isn't easily parameterized by node_id, the impl agent should add a `node_id` filter parameter to the existing function rather than duplicating it.
+- **Risk**: The web page is a Next.js Server Component with `cache: 'no-store'`. If the API is slow, the page will be slow. Keep stats fetch fire-and-forget with a short timeout or use `Promise.allSettled` so node list is never blocked by a stats failure.
+- **Assumption**: `node_measurement_summaries` contains enough data for the window to produce non-empty stats once the node is operational. If a new node has never pushed measurements, the per-node stats endpoint should return an empty-but-valid response (not 404), with a `"note": "no measurements in window"` field.
+- **Assumption**: Provider `slot_id` values in measurement summaries match the `providers` array on node registration (e.g., both use `"claude"`, not `"claude-sonnet-4-6"`). If they diverge, health dots on node cards will show grey.
